My sisters & I took our parents here for their 25th wedding anniversary. I couldn't have been more disappointed. I ordered a martini & first asked if they had blue cheese olives, the waiter said yes & then ended up bringing it to me with plain olives & said sorry I thought we had them but we don't! I was shocked that not only a high end restaurant like this didn't have blue cheese olives but that the waiter thought it ok to bring me plain olives then to come over & ask me first if that was alright. I really only wanted a martini with the blue cheese or else I would've got a different drink! I think when you're paying 16.00 for a drink it should come how it was ordered! For dinner I ordered a filet & salad. I ordered the filet medium well, it was definitely medium RARE. A medium well steak has only a hint of pink in the middle this steak was VERY PINK all the way through. I was so hungry I ate it & all night I felt so sick. I would've loved to ask kindly if I could get it cooked more but I never saw our waiter again after we got our food!!!! No one ever came by to ask how everything was! Even at the cheapest restaurants they always come to ask how everything is. I was in complete shock. I'm sorry but 40.00 for a steak, that is fine but I expect it to be cooked how I asked for it. We had a party of 11 so I didn't know until the ride home that there were 3 others in our group who had under cooked steak! My poor little niece said she thought her steak mooed at her! She took it home for mom to cook it more there. My husband liked his steak as he likes it practically raw. The salad was awful, how do you mess up a salad right?? Well they use huge pieces of romaine lettuce (the kind we use at home for sandwiches!!) It was too much of a pain to cut it, took forever. Bottom line I had nothing at all that I was happy with & I am not a picky person at all! Come to find out my Dad was one who's steak was under cooked & my brother in law told me my mom ordered bolognese with prime rib & I guess the way it was worded she was looking all over through the pasta for prime rib not realizing it was in the sauce! I felt terrible this is how their 25th wedding anniversary dinner from us turned out. I just knew we should've went to Ruth's Chris where the prices are basically the same if not cheaper & the service is always phenomenal. My sister ordered the salmon & said it was just "okay" she also is far from picky. When you are coming to a high end place like this you expect more than mediocre food & poor service! Also when we were almost done with dinner I really needed more water, I felt so dehydrated. When a woman came by to clear some plates from our table (not our waiter) I asked her if I could please have some more water. She didn't respond but I asked plenty loudly & she was right by me. So then my husband nicely asked her & she never got me any!!! Then my niece offered me hers as she never drank any. Our bill including the 20% tip we left (we all work or have worked in the customer service industry) we spent just under 1,000.00!! I definitely feel robbed. I would say the only thing enjoyable about this place is the gorgeous scenery outside & inside. There are far better places in the city that have fantastic customer service & gorgeous views. I see zero reason to ever visit Terrace 16 again. Super disappointing!

We went here sometime in the early evening before the 8pm rush for a few drinks. We were slightly underdressed but it was no problem since we were still let in. Price rating is accurate - things are a bit pricey here but I'd imagine that's to pay for the rent.  Staff were curt, but I'd imagine it's because they get a handful of Trump haters and broke folks from time to time who end up as problematic guests. There was certainly a sharpness to their attitude, nevertheless I wouldn't qualify it as full-out rudeness even if we certainly looked the part.  Prices are about $10-25 for glasses. $4 dollars-42.50 for food. The seasonal ice cream turned out to be alcoholic sorbet (negroni-based). I am a non-drinker, so after bringing this to the wait-staff's attention, the server gave me a sincere apology, and brought a vanilla custard instead.  The quality of the food and beverage is good, but the real value is in the view you pay for. We were able to stay for as long as we wanted and weren't pressured to leave even as many others joined in the evening rush, so that's a huge plus.  Much of what Terrace 16 gets right is the experience of a rooftop lounge. If they improve in their waitstaff's service, they can truly bring the five-star lounge to the five-star Trump Hotel.

A more accurate description would have been - a plate of lettuce and Cabbage in a gravy of sauce , with a garnish of octopus. Zero flavor.  Last and absolutely worst - service! Incredibly slow. I. E. They brought out our appetizer at the END of our meal. With no apology or acknowledgment of their mistake. My meal was brought about ten minutes after everyone else's. Again, no attempt made to appease the customer. The terrace was unbelievably cold and they told us we couldn't sit in an area near the gas lamps because that area wasn't served.  All in all. Extremely overpriced, with awful service and cheap substitutes for what a meal at the price listed should be. Avoid.
SAD!  This place is very overrated and the drinks are bitter and orange.  And the Chick Pee dip smells like ammonia.
Relaxing atomsphere.  We took our time and enjoyed the best view of the city - followed by Wednesday night fireworks. Our server was great, the food was great.  Come to relax and "take it all in".
We all completely regretted being there before we even got our food. Then once we got our food, it was way over. Terrible service with overpriced goods mixed with under par food = no thank you
Elegant drinks are made perfect

Attended an event for a magazine, and the terrace was the perfect backdrop for everything related to Chicago. It has great views and ample space to spread out. The cocktails that were served were delicious. Will definitely be back during warmer months.

Wish I could give it no stars. Over priced, undercooked meals prepared by 11th city players who were more interested in their audition that afternoon than finding out what was gluten free because they couldn't locate the "Death Menu" (their words overheard). Simply horrible experience.
Had drinks here, terribly overpriced for the neighborhood. Nice view, but that's all you're getting.
Service was slow. Small area. Only on 16th floor. Wish it was on a higher floor for a better view of the city.
Beautiful view! Dinks are pricy but great
Overpriced and cocktails not as good as rebar, but great view

Overpriced, and when we moved to an open couch to enjoy the view for 10 minutes while finishing our drinks, the hostess came over and told us the section was closed (even though there were others sitting nearby) due to "not enough servers". There were literally 10 servers milling around for 20 tables of patrons. We moved back to the bar and within 2 minutes other people sat where we had tried to sit and then others were seated in that section. Really? Totally insulted and disappointed, won't be back. Get it together.
Very nice view of the river and city.  Rather pricey but a nice experience on a summer day. No wifi.
Very beautiful view. It's pricey but the terrasse is beautiful and the view fantastic

It's the trump building, so you're paying a premium for the view. The outdoor terrace is worth a $14 drink on a sunny day, but it's really just a tourist stop. Buy a drink, walk around and take some photos, enjoy the sun and view, and then find a better place to spend your time out.
Great view of the city and summer fireworks. Expensive, but worth it for the views. Excellent service from friendly waitresses.

The views are worth 5 stars. Drinks and food were extremely overpriced. Spectacular views but really pretentious.  We went for one drink and I think it was worth it, but wouldn't stay for anything else.

Nice view but terrible service. Ordered drinks that where served to us after a very long wait. It was not busy at all so their is no reason for more than a 10 minor wait on simple drinks. Service is slow and with an attitude. If you want a nice view go to any other of Chicago's fine lounges, and avoid all this.

4 Stars just for the view! One of my favorite rooftop bar views in the city--- you get a bit of the river, which leads up to the lake, with a view of the Wrigley building, Tribune Tower, and just the magnificence of the Chicago Loop all around you. Drinks are pricy, from $20-25. I had the Draque, which was a sweet blueberry cocktail--- would definitely recommend. Maybe not worth $20, but it’s definitely worth paying that for the view! A great place to take visitors for sure. If only I had $100 to spare on a sundae or burger there though.
Beautiful Experience
Excellent service and venue

Elegant Rooftop Bar on the Chicago River  The Terrace at the Trump Hotel has one the best views of downtown Chicago and good cocktails too. Last summer, on a particularly clear evening, I enjoyed a nice sparkling Rosé and a friend had the "First Mate," which is an interesting twist on the classic Margarita.

The awesome view worth a million! And no surprise they do Charge you that much as well:) if you are a fan of $40 per glass wine and enjoy the view. But definitely worth checking out sometime, would be a great friends hangout or romantic date night... Make sure its in the summer season, since they actually close the terrace during the winter.

The  View at the Terrace at Trump will take your breath away. The food is average bar food and the drinks are expensive but no one really goes there for the food. If you go there around 2 pm- when they open- you'll have no problem finding a table with a great view.
My dad and i went for drinks here and the service was great! absolutely spectacularrrr view! highly recommended

#30daychallenge #Chicago Favorite date spot  You can't beat the Terrace at Trump at sunset in the city!  A cosmo, cheese plate, good friends, a nice warm south breeze and watching day turn to night...awesome! The servers are attentive but don't push.  There is a limited amount of seating because you cannot be on the terrace without a seat; and it can get BREEZY.  But, that's alfresco!

Full disclosure.  I am an employee at the Trump Hotel.  The terrace is one of the best outdoor venues to enjoy a cocktail and nosh on some delicious food while surrounded by a panoramic view of the city.  There's round tables of about 5, a long community table, smaller bar tables (as well as seats by the bar) and as long as the weather is nice, it's open.  Watching the fireworks on a saturday night during a seasonably cool summer night is quite an experience.  The themes change every year and but are very casual and fun.  The Chef prepares special dishes that are different than what you get inside the fine dining restaurant, Sixteen.  And the bartenders and servers are cheerful and accomodating.  You should try it at least once even if you live in the city.  Especially if you're visitng...
Phenomenal view.
